node.text:
Grateful to KFYR for sharing our stories as patients who continue to battle infertility! We are 1 in 8. We will continue to speak our truths despite how incredibly vulnerable and difficult it is. There is a terrible stigma that surrounds infertility and no couple should suffer alone and in silence. 🍍 🌈 👶🏼 

This bill would have made the difference for North Dakota families with infertility disease who are unable to afford the cost that far exceeds $20,000. Children are the future and no family should be denied this dream because of a lack of medical coverage and insurance denials. 

We have a lot of educating to do before we bring back the bill next year. We will continue to pound the pavement, testify before committees, send emails, speak out, lobby, meet, and advocate for families in our state.

node.text: Today my school hosted our first ever St. Jude Trike-a-thon! 🚲 We had SO many kids come out to ride to support kids receiving cancer treatment at St. Jude hospital. ❤️ Our youngest learners (ages 3-7) raised $4,000+ and counting! 🤩 Thank you to the kids, their families and friends, @alphalitfargogf , and all of the volunteers that made this event so successful! 🎉 See you next year! #stjudetrikeathon #kidshelpingkids @stjude
